==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Linotype
<hw>Lin"o*type</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Line</er>;
<er>Type</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Print.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A kind of
typesetting machine which produces castings, each of which corresponds
to a line of separate types. By pressing the keys of a keyboard like one
on a typewriter, the matrices for one line are properly arranged; the
entire line, or stereotype, or slug, is then cast and planed, and the
matrices are returned to their proper places, the whole process being
automatic.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The slug produced by the machine, or
matter composed in such lines.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Lin"o*typ`ist</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Linoxin</ent>⟦br⟧
